  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/SwapPhase.lean:2:18: * '. All rights reserved.':\n'Copyright (c) YYYY' should be followed by a space\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
   "SSExactMajority/Convergence/SwapPhase.lean:4:0: * '\n# Swap Phase: Misordered-Pair Potential\n\nIn an `Srank` configuration (all agents Settled, ranks bijective), the\n\"swap\" phase of P_EM rearranges agent states so that A-input agents\nhave lower ranks than B-input agents ã i.e., the configuration enters\n`Sswap`.\n\nWe measure progress by the count of *misordered pairs*:\n\n  > A pair `(u, v)` is misordered iff\n  > `(C u).2 = .B ãÏ (C v).2 = .A ãÏ (C u).1.rank < (C v).1.rank`.\n\nThis file establishes the foundational potential function:\n\n  * `MisorderedPair` ã the predicate on agent pairs.\n  * `misorderedSet`, `misorderedCount` ã the witness Finset and its\n    cardinality (a decidable potential).\n  * `mem_misorderedSet`, `misorderedCount_eq_zero_iff` ã basic\n    rewriting lemmas.\n  * `exists_misordered_of_pos_count` ã extracting an explicit witness\n    when the count is positive.\n\nThe `Srank ãÏ no-misorder ã¿ Sswap` characterization and the deterministic\nscheduler driving the potential to zero are layered on top of these.':\nIf an authors line spans multiple lines, each line but the last must end with a trailing comma\n\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
